I think  would read better. Alternatively, consider giving an approximate time of day to maintain consistency with the rest of the document?




Overall, this was good and I enjoyed it very much. I dug the thematic elements, the gentle inclusion of your own GoI in the Church of Iðunn, the backdoor politics and slimy business dealings, seeing a weaker than usual Foundation caught on their back foot, and so on. There was a lot to like here and not a lot to distract me from said enjoyment outside of the odd headcanon conflict or syntaxial awkwardness. The final reveal that the Foundation is now containing and abusing -1 in much the same way that Coca-Cola was doing before, thus drawing the parallel between the two organizations, was expected, but honestly it served to the benefit of the piece. It's a little glimpse into the bleak reality of the situation. Never once was the deity even thought about as anything other than a cog in the greater machine. Ultimately, Candler was rightthe Foundation was in no position to judge. Easy +1.

